@startuml memo-lifecycle
title Memo Lifecycle — Capture, Hygiene, Routing
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam BackgroundColor #fafafa
skinparam ArrowColor #000000
skinparam ArrowFontColor #000000
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam nodesep 16
skinparam ranksep 26
hide stereotype

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #d6e6f5
  BorderColor #1f4768
  FontColor #111
  RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #f5ead5
  BorderColor #5a4319
  FontColor #111
}
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #e0d4ec
  BorderColor #5a3a72
  FontColor #111
}
skinparam package {
  FontColor #111
  FontSize 13
  FontStyle bold
  BorderColor #444
  BorderThickness 2
}

package "SPEC SIDE" as SpecPkg #fde8ec {
  rectangle "/livespec:doctor" as Doctor
  rectangle "/livespec:propose-changes" as Propose
  database "SPECIFICATION/" as Spec #f5d76e
  database "proposed_changes/" as PCQueue
}

package "IMPLEMENTATION SIDE" as ImplPkg #e3f0e3 {
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\ncapture-memo" as CaptureMemo
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\nprocess-memos" as ProcessMemos
  rectangle "/livespec-impl-*:\nlist-memos\n(thin transport)" as ListMemos #ccddee
  component "Spec Reader" as SpecReader

  database "Memos\n(plugin-specific:\nbd Dolt / JSONL / ...)" as Memos
  database "Work Items" as WorkItems
  database "Persistent\nAgent Knowledge\n(harness instruction files,\nlong-lived memory store, ...)" as AgentKnowledge #f5d76e
}

' Capture path — low-friction free-text deposit
CaptureMemo --> Memos : writes pending memo

' Doctor queries untriaged memos via the list-memos thin-transport skill
' (replaces the pre-2026-05-18 machine-only query surface)
Memos --> ListMemos : read state
ListMemos -[#a02020,thickness=2]-> Doctor : list-memos\n--filter=untriaged --json\n(hygiene invariant)

' Spec Reader feeds Process Memos for spec-vs-impl disposition decisions
Spec -[#a02020,thickness=2]-> SpecReader
SpecReader --> ProcessMemos

' Process Memos drains pending memos and routes per disposition
Memos --> ProcessMemos
ProcessMemos --> WorkItems : impl-bound\n(freeform work item)
ProcessMemos --> AgentKnowledge : persistent-knowledge\n(graduate the memo)
ProcessMemos --> Memos : discard\n(state marker)

' Cross-boundary: spec-bound memo routes to Propose Change
ProcessMemos -[#a02020,thickness=2]-> Propose : spec-bound
Propose --> PCQueue

note right of Memos : Queue + archive — dispositioned memos\nremain with a state marker for audit\n(spec-bound, impl-bound,\npersistent-knowledge, discard). Transient\nby construction: every memo MUST\neventually flow to spec, impl, persistent\nknowledge, or discard. Rejects the\npermanent-memory-store pattern from\ntools like bd remember.

note bottom of Doctor : Hygiene invariant: "no untriaged memo MUST\nremain unresolved beyond N days." Doctor\ninvokes the impl plugin's list-memos\nthin-transport skill (the 2026-05-18\nresolution to the prior machine-only\nquery surface). Doctor does NOT know how\nmemos get resolved — only that they should be.

note right of ProcessMemos : Per-memo handholding skill — walks each\npending memo via user dialogue with four\ndispositions. The handholding principle\nis load-bearing: users do not manually\ninvoke propose-changes for spec-bound memos;\nprocess-memos drives them through the\nappropriate downstream skill.

note bottom of AgentKnowledge : Long-term agent knowledge that doesn't fit\nas a spec requirement or as inline code.\nForm is implementation-dependent: file-based\nrealizations use harness instruction files\n(AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md / .ai/<topic>.md);\nother plugins may use a long-lived memory\nstore the agent queries at relevant points.

@enduml
